abstract: Wall Street's major indexes resumed their rally with fresh records on Thursday as U.S. Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin said an initial U.S.-China trade deal would be signed in early January.
snippet: Wall Street's major indexes resumed their rally with fresh records on Thursday as U.S. Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin said an initial U.S.-China trade deal would be signed in early January.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Wall Street's major indexes resumed their rally with fresh records on Thursday as U.S. Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin said an initial U.S.-China trade deal would be signed in early January.
headline_main: Record-Setting Rally Resumes as Mnuchin Says Trade Deal to Be Signed
headline_print_headline: Record-Setting Rally Resumes as Mnuchin Says Trade Deal to Be Signed

abstract: The number of Americans filing applications for unemployment benefits dropped from a more than two-year high last week, pointing to sustained labor market strength that should continue to underpin consumer spending and the economy.
snippet: The number of Americans filing applications for unemployment benefits dropped from a more than two-year high last week, pointing to sustained labor market strength that should continue to underpin consumer spending and the economy.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The number of Americans filing applications for unemployment benefits dropped from a more than two-year high last week, pointing to sustained labor market strength that should continue to underpin consumer spending and the economy.
headline_main: U.S. Labor Market on Solid Ground; Mid-Atlantic Factories Sputter
headline_print_headline: U.S. Labor Market on Solid Ground; Mid-Atlantic Factories Sputter

abstract: As President Donald Trump girds for a U.S. Senate impeachment trial, he is entrusting the future of his presidency to someone widely known as a shrewd negotiator who also plays hardball politics at a level unusual even by Washington standards.

abstract: China on Thursday urged the United States and North Korea to resume dialogue and work to resolve disagreements as soon as possible amid renewed tensions between Washington and Pyongyang over the latter's nuclear and missiles programs.
snippet: China on Thursday urged the United States and North Korea to resume dialogue and work to resolve disagreements as soon as possible amid renewed tensions between Washington and Pyongyang over the latter's nuclear and missiles programs.
lead_paragraph: BEIJING — China on Thursday urged the United States and North Korea to resume dialogue and work to resolve disagreements as soon as possible amid renewed tensions between Washington and Pyongyang over the latter's nuclear and missiles programs.
headline_main: China Urges U.S., North Korea to Resume Talks as Tensions Escalate
headline_print_headline: China Urges U.S., North Korea to Resume Talks as Tensions Escalate

abstract: U.S. Democrats on Thursday pressed the Republican-controlled Senate to call Donald Trump's top lieutenants to testify in its trial of the impeached president, as they sought to focus attention on the trial ahead of the 2020 presidential election.
snippet: U.S. Democrats on Thursday pressed the Republican-controlled Senate to call Donald Trump's top lieutenants to testify in its trial of the impeached president, as they sought to focus attention on the trial ahead of the 2020 presidential election.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. Democrats on Thursday pressed the Republican-controlled Senate to call Donald Trump's top lieutenants to testify in its trial of the impeached president, as they sought to focus attention on the trial ahead of the 2020 presidential election.
headline_main: Democrats Seek High-Profile Trial for Trump in Senate
headline_print_headline: Democrats Seek High-Profile Trial for Trump in Senate

abstract: Rising Democratic candidate Pete Buttigieg came under attack during a debate among U.S. presidential hopefuls on Thursday, as his rivals questioned his lack of Washington experience and criticized his fundraising from wealthy donors.
snippet: Rising Democratic candidate Pete Buttigieg came under attack during a debate among U.S. presidential hopefuls on Thursday, as his rivals questioned his lack of Washington experience and criticized his fundraising from wealthy donors.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Rising Democratic candidate Pete Buttigieg came under attack during a debate among U.S. presidential hopefuls on Thursday, as his rivals questioned his lack of Washington experience and criticized his fundraising from wealthy donors.
headline_main: Wine Caves and Billionaires: Buttigieg Under Fire Over Fundraising at Democratic Debate
headline_print_headline: Wine Caves and Billionaires: Buttigieg Under Fire Over Fundraising at Democratic Debate

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump called Boeing Chief Executive Dennis Muilenburg this week to ask about the status of 737 MAX production, two people briefed on the matter confirmed.

abstract: The departures leave our critical infrastructure, elections, data and networks vulnerable.
snippet: The departures leave our critical infrastructure, elections, data and networks vulnerable.
lead_paragraph: At the end of 2019, with less than a year to go until the presidential election, the government official who has been leading efforts to secure voting systems in the United States will leave the Department of Homeland Security to join Google. The impending departure of Jeanette Manfra, the assistant director for cybersecurity at the department’s Cybersecurity and Infrastructure Security Agency, is a major loss for the federal government’s civilian cybersecurity efforts, and it comes at the end of a year that saw a series of departures by key cybersecurity personnel.

lead_paragraph: HERMOSILLO, Mexico — The heavy-set man swept through a nightclub curtain into the reserved area of a nightclub. In the darkness he agreed to talk about his business: handling the income from smuggling migrants across a 375-mile stretch of the U.S.-Mexico border.
headline_main: What Crackdown? Migrant Smuggling Business Adapts, Thrives
